channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Notre Dame Fighting Irish Unveil Updated Home Football Jerseys
item.description: Although they leaked in the very first screenshot of EA Sports' College Football 25 back in May, Notre Dame revealed several small changes to its standard home jerseys on Friday morning.

item.title: Mauricio Umansky Snuggles Up With Actress Nikita Kahn In Greece
item.description: Mauricio Umansky is logging some quality time with actress Nikita Kahn over in Greece ... snuggling up at a famous beach club and looking very much like a cute new couple. TMZ obtained photos and videos of Mauricio and Nikita at Scorpios Beach Club…

item.title: Barcelona, Arsenal, Bayern Munich Headline Busy Week in European Kit Launches
item.description: Plus plenty other recent kit unveilings from Germany's Bundesliga, La Liga in Spain, English Premier League, Italy's Serie A and French Ligue 1

item.title: Philadelphia Gunwoman Allegedly Shoots Baby, Parents Flee Without Him
item.description: A seven-month-old baby in Philadelphia is miraculously in stable condition after being shot and left to fend for himself -- with his ordeal caught on distressing CCTV footage. Take a look at your own discretion ... a couple was out for a stroll…

item.title: Oregon Ducks Unveil Green “Generation O” Football Uniforms
item.description: Oregon has unveiled the second combination of its new "Generation O" uniforms, which pay homage to the "Gang Green" Ducks of the mid-1990s.

item.title: Richard Simmons' Cause of Death Still Unknown, Buried in L.A.
item.description: Richard Simmons' death certificate sheds no further light on the mystery surrounding his death ... but does provide some interesting details on his final resting place. In the document obtained by TMZ ... Richard's manner of death is not listed --…

item.title: MLB Players to Wear Hall of Fame Patches on Caps This Weekend
item.description: Major League Baseball will celebrate the 85th anniversary of the National Baseball Hall of Fame this weekend by having all 30 of its teams wear the museum’s logo on the side of their caps this weekend. item.description: Throwback Weekend logos depict smiling cartoon mascots while uniforms feature large black letters or wordmarks on the front
